      <unittitle encodinganalog="245">Lloyd C. Douglas Papers <unitdate type="inclusive" encodinganalog="245$f" normal="1900/1954">1900-1954</unitdate></unittitle>
      <abstract>Popular novelist, author of The Robe and Magnificent Obsession, and minister of the First Congregational Church of Ann Arbor, Michigan. Correspondence with his family, publishers and other authors concerning his work and including comments on national politics, Presidents Franklin D. Roosevelt and Harry S. Truman, and World War II; also manuscripts of addresses, articles, sermons, and novels; scrapbooks; and photographs.</abstract>
